org.energy_home.jemma.zgd
Class GalExtenderProxy

java.lang.Object
  org.energy_home.jemma.zgd.GalExtenderProxy
All Implemented Interfaces:
GatewayInterface, IGalExtender
public class GalExtenderProxy
extends java.lang.Object
implements IGalExtender

Proxy object for GalController object. The proxy pattern enables the management of multiple concurrent clients. Each client instantiates a proxy with its unique identifier that distinguishes it between other proxy's objects.

The mechanism used by the Gal controller is simple: every time a client requests to the Gal controller the execution of one of its methods, the proxy adds its identifier to that request. After a while, when the response will become available to the Gal controller, it uses that identifier to find the right proxy destination (the client) to dispatch the response to it.

Author:
"Ing. Marco Nieddu or from Consoft Sistemi S.P.A., financed by EIT ICT Labs activity SecSES - Secure Energy Systems (activity id 13030)"
